{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a2d3e88c-8433-4fe5-81fe-396350e80940","content":"In .NET 10, `dotnet test` uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform **natively** — you no longer need the `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property. That property was the opt-in bridge for .NET 9 and earlier SDKs.\n\nWith SDK 10.0.100, just remove it:\n\n```xml\n<TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n```\n\nYour project already has `EnableMSTestRunner` set, which produces the MTP-based executable host. That's all you need — `dotnet test` will communicate with it directly via the MTP protocol.\n\nWant me to remove that property from your `.csproj`?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"b2bf0e74-66d0-48f7-9ca9-168037622e9c","outputTokens":173,"requestId":"E3CE:3D745E:1C31084:1F2E636:6A052095"},"id":"2b98ba34-1c1d-4458-b240-b582feeee9aa","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:08:42.655Z","parentId":"1bcf5c66-b085-49f0-8d9b-708cd8f826d8"}
